episodes.title: Epstein Files Fuel Clinton Vs GOP Showdown: Bill In Contempt For Rejecting Testimony | Watch
episodes.description:
The Republican-led House Oversight Committee says it will move to hold Bill Clinton in contempt of Congress after he refused to appear for a scheduled deposition tied to the Epstein probe. Oversight Chair James Comer accuses Clinton’s legal team of months of delays and defiance of what he calls a lawful subpoena. The committee had also subpoenaed Hillary Clinton, with House Speaker Mike Johnson warning that skipping testimony could trigger contempt proceedings. In a sharply worded response, the Clintons argue the subpoenas are legally invalid, unconstitutional, and an unprecedented overreach by Congress. They deny any wrongdoing and say they are prepared to fight the matter in court. Photos released by the committee show Bill Clinton alongside Jeffrey Epstein and Ghislaine Maxwell in the early 2000s. Clinton has acknowledged flying on Epstein’s plane for foundation-related travel before Epstein faced criminal charges, but insists he was unaware of Epstein’s crimes and cut ties years before Epstein’s 2006 arrest.

episodes.title: Epstein Files ‘DISGRACE’ Ex-UK Prince: Victim Goes Nuclear Against Andrew | ‘Not Okay To Ignore…’
episodes.description:
Survivors of convicted sex offender Jeffrey Epstein are demanding that former UK royal Prince Andrew face justice in the United States. Following the release of new Epstein files, victims and lawyers say powerful figures have been shielded for far too long. Epstein survivor Marina Lacerda and the late Virginia Giuffre’s legal team are calling for accountability, citing documents that appear to link Prince Andrew to Epstein’s inner circle and to Ghislaine Maxwell. The revelations have reignited global outrage and renewed pressure on US and UK authorities to act, as survivors insist the truth can no longer be ignored.

episodes.title: Epstein Recorded Trump & Clinton’s Compromising Videos? Epstein Files Reveal Disturbing Claims
episodes.description:
Newly released FBI documents connected to the Jeffrey Epstein investigation include explosive claims about alleged secret video tapes involving powerful figures like Donald Trump and Bill Clinton. An FBI tip from 2020 describes allegations that Epstein filmed compromising material across multiple states and on private jets, possibly using recordings as leverage. Court records also reference an “Adult Video Club” rental agreement for video tapes and equipment, echoing long-standing suspicions about hidden recordings. There is no public proof the tapes exist, but the documents are reigniting intense questions about what investigators were told — and what evidence may still be hidden.

episodes.title: Trump-Epstein Link EXPLODES: DOJ 'Kills' Viral FBI File On Rape Charge From Library, Then Warns...
episodes.description:
A fresh release of Jeffrey Epstein documents has reignited scrutiny around President Donald Trump — but also triggered an unusually forceful response from the Justice Department. Newly disclosed FBI records detail a pre-election phone call alleging sexual assault involving Trump and Epstein, claims the DOJ says are “unfounded and false.” Within hours of the documents becoming public, the FBI file containing the allegation was quietly removed from the DOJ’s Epstein database. At the same time, internal Justice Department emails revealed that Trump flew on Epstein’s private jet more times than previously known — information prosecutors described as “situational awareness,” not evidence of wrongdoing. As nearly 30,000 pages of Epstein-related files flood the public domain, the case underscores a familiar tension in Washington: transparency versus proof, allegation versus evidence — and why some names continue to dominate the fallout from Epstein’s shadowy past.

episodes.title: Epstein Files ‘DESTROY’ Ex-UK Prince; Emails Show Andrew Asking Maxwell For ‘Inappropriate Friends’
episodes.description:
Newly released Epstein files have reignited scrutiny around former Prince Andrew after emails surfaced using the coded phrase “two-legged sightseeing.” The documents show Ghislaine Maxwell acting as an intermediary in travel plans and personal arrangements for a man identified as “The Invisible Man,” widely believed to be Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor. The emails date back to 2001 and 2002 and add fresh context to long-standing allegations and questions about access, privilege, and secrecy within Epstein’s network. While the documents do not prove criminal wrongdoing, they have pushed Prince Andrew back into the global spotlight as more Epstein files continue to surface.

episodes.title: Clinton Camp Snaps At Trump's DOJ; Wants All Epstein Files Out & Warns ‘SOMEONE BEING PROTECTED’
episodes.description:
Former US President Bill Clinton has been pulled back into the Jeffrey Epstein debate after his spokesman publicly demanded the Justice Department release all remaining Epstein files that mention or include photos of the former president. The Clinton camp accuses the DOJ of selective transparency, warning that partial releases create insinuations rather than clarity. The controversy follows the release of Epstein documents showing Clinton in photographs, though no wrongdoing has been alleged. Even President Donald Trump weighed in, defending Clinton and criticizing how the files were released. As pressure mounts, lawmakers and Epstein survivors are demanding full disclosure.

episodes.title: Lori Vallow Daybell LIVE | 'You LIAR': High Drama As Cult Mom Sentenced In Arizona Murder Plot
episodes.description:
Lori Vallow Daybell—the so‑called “Doomsday mom”—has received two additional life sentences in Arizona, each to run consecutively alongside her existing Idaho convictions. Already imprisoned for the murders of her children and a romantic rival, Vallow Daybell is now also condemned for conspiring to murder her estranged husband, Charles Vallow, and her niece’s ex‑husband, Brandon Boudreaux. During the sentencing, Judge Justin Beresky declared that her crimes—born of cult‑like beliefs and calculation—marshaled a “wake of destruction” across multiple states. He made clear: this woman should never be free.
